{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_autumnal_equinox/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>It's clear that change is on its way,<br>\nFor it's seen that light has less sway,<br>\nSo darkness can't be kept at bay,<br>\nAnd stopped from eroding the day<br>\nDarkness fights so to reign the sky,<br>\nPoised against light it draws a tie,<br>\nWhich simply does not satisfy,<br>\nBut balance shifts as time goes by,<br>\nThe change can be felt in the air,<br>\nA change that will soon make trees bare,<br>\nA change through which it's hard to fare,<br>\nAs its effects show everywhere,<br>\nThe day becomes perfectly split,<br>\nHalf is dark and the other lit,<br>\nThe clockwork of nature bids it,<br>\nIt's what mother nature sees fit.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 09, 2020","title":"Autumnal Equinox","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/18425a9a87aa5e3caee15f52883c4aaf/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 09 Autumnal equinox.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/8ba556e8ba0eed0062b5ebb216e1bea8/7d509/nature_poem_autumnal_equinox.jpg","srcSet":"/static/8ba556e8ba0eed0062b5ebb216e1bea8/f836f/nature_poem_autumnal_equinox.jpg 200w,\n/static/8ba556e8ba0eed0062b5ebb216e1bea8/2244e/nature_poem_autumnal_equinox.jpg 400w,\n/static/8ba556e8ba0eed0062b5ebb216e1bea8/7d509/nature_poem_autumnal_equinox.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_autumnal_equinox/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}